An Iyaganku magistrate court yesterday sentenced a 25-year-old man, Mutiu Fatai, to one week community service and 12 stroke of cane for stealing one infinix Hot three phone, valued at N48,000. The accused was arraigned before the President of the court, Justice A.A. Adebisi on two-count charge of conspiracy and stealing. The prosecutor, Mrs. Shalewa Hammed, told the court ‎that the convict and others at large on April 9, 2017 at Oni and Son’s hospital area of Ibadan, the Oyo State capital, conspired with others to commit felony and stealing. She said on the same date, time and place, crossed the car of one Mrs. Taylor Funmilayo of Oni memorial hospital with their motorcycle and snatched her Phone valued at N48,000.00 . Hammed said the offence is contrary Section 516 and 390 (9) of the Criminal Code Cap 38 Vol.II laws of Oyo state of Nigeria, 2000 and punishable under the law. She noted that the convict had pleaded not guilty on 23 April, 2018 and was granted bail of the sum of 50,000.00 with one surety while the case was adjourned till June 7, 2018. After listening to the their argument, the Chief magistrate sentenced the suspect to 12 strokes of ‎ the cane and one week community service to serve as deterrent to others.